<% include ../partials/header.html.ejs %>

  <section class="grid intro">
    <div class="grid-cell grid8 intro__text">
      <div class="top-content" style="color: <%= pageData.current.color %>">
        <!-- <img src="/images/reporting/top-thumbs.png" alt="" style="max-width: 80%; margin: 1rem 0"> -->
        <p>Playground XYZ offer a full-service mobile advertising platform, where advertisers can create and deploy mobile advertising campaigns.</p>
        <p>Our online platform required a Reporting Dashboard for clients to monitor and gain insights on the performance of their ad placements. I designed and prototyped the <strong>Campaigns Listing </strong> and <strong>Reporting and Analytics</strong>          screens.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
    <div class="grid-cell grid4 credits">
      <div class="top-content">
        <h3>My Work</h3>
        <p>UX Research, Design, Prototype </p>
      </div>
  </section>

  <section class="grid">
    <div class="grid-cell grid4">
      <h2>Campaigns Listing</h2>
      <p>Playground customers are usually managing multiple ad campaigns at once, each containing multiple ad creatives and audience targetting.</p>
      <p>My challenge was to provide users with immediate insight into the performance of their campaigns on login.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-cell grid8 single-image">
      <img src="/images/reporting/dashboard1.jpg" alt="" style="align-self: flex-end">
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="grid">
    <div class="grid-cell grid7 single-image">
      <img src="/images/reporting/analytics1.jpg" alt="">
    </div>
    <div class="grid-cell grid5">
      <h2>Reporting and Analytics</h2>
      <p>We wanted to provide customers with custom, easily comprehensible visualisations of their Campaign Data.</p>
      <p>We also aimed to provide some basic analytics controls, so the data could be split and viewed in a number of ways to gain deeper insights on campaign performance, such as which targetted audience was responding most to the ads based on clicks or
        engagement.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>


  <section class="grid slider-section">
    <h2 style="width:100%">Key Features</h2>
    <div class="grid-cell grid3 captions-cell">
      <div class="slider__count">
        <span class="current-count"></span>
        <span class="full-count"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="slider__captions" id="slider-campaigns-captions">
        <div class="caption current">
          <h4>Campaigns, Creatives, Placements</h4>
          <p> Overview of your campaigns can be expanded to display the ad creatives for each campaign, whether ad placement is delivering and generating engagement form its target audience.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="caption">
          <h4>Visual insights</h4>
          <p>Custom charts quickly surface the most relevant data for campaign managers, including alerts when key metrics for a campaign are not hitting their benchmarks.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="caption">
          <h4>Annotations and Alerts</h4>
          <p>Customers are quickly alerted when the data indicates a placement is not performing to benchmarks. Annotations keep track of where optimisations were made during the campaign to improve campaign performance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="caption">
          <h4>Basic Analytics</h4>
          <p>Campaign data can be split and grouped in various ways - by placement, audience and site. Animated transitions and color coding assist clients to make comparisons and gain insights</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="slider__nav" id="slider-campaigns-nav">
        <svg class="slider__arrow slider__arrow--left" viewBox="0 0 300 300" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
          <use x="0" y="0" href="#arrow-left"></use>
        </svg>
        <svg class="slider__arrow slider__arrow--right" viewBox="0 0 300 300" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
          <use x="0" y="0" href="#arrow-right"></use>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-cell grid9 slider-cell">

      <div id="slider-campaigns" class="slider--desktop">

        <!-- image and content -->
