          </video>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>

  </section>

  <section class="grid additional-features" style="background: <%= color.palegrey %>;">
    <h2 style="width:100%;">Additional Features</h2>
    <div class="grid-cell grid6">
      <img src="/images/reporting/preview-creative.jpg" alt="" style="align-self: center; width: 100%">
      <h4>Ad previews</h4>
      <p>Ad Creative can be viewed as a preview to show advertisers what their customers are seeing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-cell grid6">
      <img src="/images/reporting/download-sheet.jpg" alt="" style="align-self: center; width: 100%">
      <h4>Data downloads</h4>
      <p>All data is downloadable as a formatted Excel document for further analysis.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="grid process">
    <h2 style="width:100%">Process</h2>
    <div class="grid-cell grid6 process-hero">
      <img src="/images/process-reporting.png" alt="">
    </div>
    <div class="grid-cell grid6">
      <p>
        <svg viewBox="0 0 300 300" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
          <use x="0" y="0" href="#research"></use>
        </svg> Gathered user FAQs and most requested campaign insights user input through our Operations Team, based on two years of managing campaigns and reporting in-house.</p>

      <p>
        <svg viewBox="0 0 300 300" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
          <use x="0" y="0" href="#plan"></use>
        </svg> Wireframed the application using Balsamiq mockups over several iterations until we hit on the most clear and efficient layout.</p>

      <p>
        <svg viewBox="0 0 300 300" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
          <use x="0" y="0" href="#codesign"></use>
        </svg> Built the prototype with HTML / CSS / JS, using the Amcharts API for the more complex charts. I also created a ‘dummy data’ generator with Javascript, with which we could simulate errors to see how the interface would respond.</p>
    </div>
  </section>



